A student wants to add 5 to every element of a vector using a range-based for loop, but the vector is unchanged afterward. What is wrong?

```cpp
#include <vector>

int main()
{
    std::vector<int> v { 10, 20, 30 };
    for (int x : v)
        x += 5;   // student expects v to hold {15, 25, 35}
}
